{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"70c11df2-fba2-489a-a88f-cfa372bd398d","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — only run tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also use `DisplayName~` instead of `FullyQualifiedName~` if you prefer matching on the shorter display name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"28e6a2ff-54ed-450a-b5a6-2c26cabe4860","outputTokens":157,"requestId":"A032:AFC07:19DF0E1:1D6090C:69FE9241"},"id":"10274cfb-b47a-43dc-9a06-234f813f02eb","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:47:49.663Z","parentId":"ee7476bf-0efa-42b8-95e5-d501824cd434"}
